### Profile Image Management API Examples
### This file demonstrates the profile image upload and delete functionality

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8081/api
@token = Bearer your-jwt-token-here

### 1. Upload Profile Image
POST {{baseUrl}}/files/profile-image
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="profile.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-images/profile.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### Expected Response:
### {
###   "message": "Profile image uploaded successfully",
###   "imageUrl": "/api/uploads/profile-images/uuid-filename.jpg"
### }

### 2. Delete Profile Image
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/files/profile-image
Authorization: {{token}}

### Expected Response:
### {
###   "message": "Profile image deleted successfully"
### }

### 3. Get User Profile (to verify image URL)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: {{token}}

### Expected Response includes:
### {
###   "profileImageUrl": "/api/uploads/profile-images/uuid-filename.jpg" or null
### }

### Notes:
### - Only authenticated users can upload/delete profile images
### - Supported formats: JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP
### - Maximum file size: 5MB
### - Images are stored in uploads/profile-images/ directory
### - Delete operation removes the physical file and sets profileImageUrl to null
### - Frontend automatically falls back to role-based default avatars after deletion